The paper discusses the challenge of simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) in robotics, autonomous vehicles, and virtual and augmented reality, which are all related to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of visual understanding (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI) in developing SLAM algorithms. The paper also discusses the need for optimization of heterogeneous, accelerated architectures (cs.SY) and the use of end-to-end simulation tools (cs.LG) for SLAM.
